gomodel:SYNGO_4839  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"To test whether Piccolo knockdown could inhibit activity-dependent EGFP-actin clustering, we infected neurons with either EGFP-actin or EGFP-actin/Pclo28 constructs, and compared the changes in fluorescence intensity and number/unit axon length of EGFP-actin clusters before and after 90 mm KCl depolarization.\n\nStrikingly, neurons lacking Piccolo had less punctate, more diffuse distributions of axonal EGFP-actin under basal conditions (Fig. 6B,C,E), and dramatically decreased clustering of presynaptic EGFP-actin following high-K+ depolarization (Fig. 6B,D,E). A similar attenuation of EGFP-actin clustering was seen in wild-type neurons pretreated with the actin depolymerizing drug latrunculin A (Fig. 6A,D,E).\n\nSimilarly, we found that jasplakinolide induced EGFP-actin clustering in Pclo28-expressing neurons (Fig. 6C-E), indicating that these neurons were still capable of F-actin polymerization. However, <40% of these clusters colocalized with presynaptic markers compared with ~70% in wild-type neurons (Fig. 5C), further indicating that presynaptic F-actin assembly was specifically impaired in the absence of Piccolo.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Mouse hippocampal cultures were similarly prepared from P0-P1 pups\"\n\nAntibody:\n\"Antibodies against Piccolo (rabbit) and MAP2 (rabbit and mouse) were used as previously described\" PMID:10833299." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4839" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

